- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possibility because the paper discusses the behavior of agents in a network and how they communicate with each other. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible because the paper presents a tool for simulating and analyzing the behavior of complex systems (i.e., networks of agents).
